9 /// \file This file implements the LiveInterval analysis pass which is used ----
10 /// by the Linear Scan Register allocator. This pass linearizes the ----
11 /// basic blocks of the function in DFS order and computes live intervals for ----
12 /// each virtual and physical register. ----

257 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
258 // Register Unit Liveness ----
259 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
260 // ----
261 // Fixed interference typically comes from ABI boundaries: Function arguments ----
262 // and return values are passed in fixed registers, and so are exception ----
263 // pointers entering landing pads. Certain instructions require values to be ----
264 // present in specific registers. That is also represented through fixed ----
265 // interference. ----
266 // ----

269 /// aliasing registers. The range should be empty, or contain only dead ----
270 /// phi-defs from ABI blocks. ----

392 const MachineBasicBlock *MBB = Indexes->getMBBFromIndex(Idx.getPrevSlot()); 0
393 SlotIndex BlockStart = Indexes->getMBBStartIdx(MBB); 0
394 ----
395 // Extend the live range for VNI to be live at Idx. ----
396 if (VNInfo *ExtVNI = Segments.extendInBlock(BlockStart, Idx)) { 0
397 assert(ExtVNI == VNI && "Unexpected existing value number"); 0
398 (void)ExtVNI; ----
399 // Is this a PHIDef we haven't seen before? ----
400 if (!VNI->isPHIDef() || VNI->def != BlockStart || 0
401 !UsedPHIs.insert(VNI).second) 0
402 continue; 0
403 // The PHI is live, make sure the predecessors are live-out. ----
404 for (const MachineBasicBlock *Pred : MBB->predecessors()) { 0
405 if (!LiveOut.insert(Pred).second) 0
406 continue; 0
407 SlotIndex Stop = Indexes->getMBBEndIdx(Pred); 0
408 // A predecessor is not required to have a live-out value for a PHI. ----
409 if (VNInfo *PVNI = OldRange.getVNInfoBefore(Stop)) 0
410 WorkList.push_back(std::make_pair(Stop, PVNI)); 0
411 } ----
412 continue; 0
413 } 0
414 ----
415 // VNI is live-in to MBB. ----
416 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " live-in at " << BlockStart << '\n'); 0
417 Segments.addSegment(LiveRange::Segment(BlockStart, Idx, VNI)); 0
418 ----
419 // Make sure VNI is live-out from the predecessors. ----
420 for (const MachineBasicBlock *Pred : MBB->predecessors()) { 0
421 if (!LiveOut.insert(Pred).second) 0
422 continue; 0
423 SlotIndex Stop = Indexes->getMBBEndIdx(Pred); 0
424 if (VNInfo *OldVNI = OldRange.getVNInfoBefore(Stop)) { 0
425 assert(OldVNI == VNI && "Wrong value out of predecessor"); 0
426 (void)OldVNI; ----
427 WorkList.push_back(std::make_pair(Stop, VNI)); 0
428 } else { ----
429 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
430 // There was no old VNI. Verify that Stop is jointly dominated ----
431 // by s for this live range. ----
432 assert(LaneMask.any() && 0
433 "Missing value out of predecessor for main range"); ----
434 SmallVector Undefs; 0
435 LI.computeSubRangeUndefs(Undefs, LaneMask, *MRI, *Indexes); 0
436 assert(LiveRangeCalc::isJointlyDominated(Pred, Undefs, *Indexes) && 0
437 "Missing value out of predecessor for subrange"); ----
438 #endif ----
439 } 0
440 } ----
441 } ----
442 } 0
443 ----
444 bool LiveIntervals::shrinkToUses(LiveInterval *li, 0
445 SmallVectorImpl *dead) { ----
446 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Shrink: " << *li << '\n'); 0
447 assert(li->reg().isVirtual() && "Can only shrink virtual registers"); 0
448 ----
449 // Shrink subregister live ranges. ----
450 bool NeedsCleanup = false; 0
451 for (LiveInterval::SubRange &S : li->subranges()) { 0
452 shrinkToUses(S, li->reg()); 0
453 if (S.empty()) 0
454 NeedsCleanup = true; 0
455 } ----
456 if (NeedsCleanup) 0
457 li->removeEmptySubRanges(); 0
458 ----
459 // Find all the values used, including PHI kills. ----
460 ShrinkToUsesWorkList WorkList; 0
461 ----
462 // Visit all instructions reading li->reg(). ----
463 Register Reg = li->reg(); 0
464 for (MachineInstr &UseMI : MRI->reg_instructions(Reg)) { 0
465 if (UseMI.isDebugInstr() || !UseMI.readsVirtualRegister(Reg)) 0
466 continue; 0
467 SlotIndex Idx = getInstructionIndex(UseMI).getRegSlot(); 0
468 LiveQueryResult LRQ = li->Query(Idx); 0
469 VNInfo *VNI = LRQ.valueIn(); 0
470 if (!VNI) { 0
471 // This shouldn't happen: readsVirtualRegister returns true, but there is ----
472 // no live value. It is likely caused by a target getting flags ----
473 // wrong. ----
474 LLVM_DEBUG( 0
475 dbgs() << Idx << '\t' << UseMI ----
476 << "Warning: Instr claims to read non-existent value in " ----
477 << *li << '\n'); ----
478 continue; 0
479 } ----
480 // Special case: An early-clobber tied operand reads and writes the ----
481 // register one slot early. ----
482 if (VNInfo *DefVNI = LRQ.valueDefined()) 0
483 Idx = DefVNI->def; 0
484 ----
485 WorkList.push_back(std::make_pair(Idx, VNI)); 0
486 } ----
487 ----
488 // Create new live ranges with only minimal live segments per def. ----
489 LiveRange NewLR; 0
490 createSegmentsForValues(NewLR, li->vnis()); 0
491 extendSegmentsToUses(NewLR, WorkList, Reg, LaneBitmask::getNone()); 0
492 ----
493 // Move the trimmed segments back. ----
494 li->segments.swap(NewLR.segments); 0
495 ----
496 // Handle dead values. ----
497 bool CanSeparate = computeDeadValues(*li, dead); 0
498 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Shrunk: " << *li << '\n'); 0
499 return CanSeparate; 0
500 } 0

524 continue; 16 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll

546 void LiveIntervals::shrinkToUses(LiveInterval::SubRange &SR, Register Reg) { 0
547 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Shrink: " << SR << '\n'); 0
548 assert(Reg.isVirtual() && "Can only shrink virtual registers"); 0
549 // Find all the values used, including PHI kills. ----
550 ShrinkToUsesWorkList WorkList; 0
551 ----
552 // Visit all instructions reading Reg. ----
553 SlotIndex LastIdx; 0
554 for (MachineOperand &MO : MRI->use_nodbg_operands(Reg)) { 0
555 // Skip "undef" uses. ----
556 if (!MO.readsReg()) 0
557 continue; 0
558 // Maybe the operand is for a subregister we don't care about. ----
559 unsigned SubReg = MO.getSubReg(); 0
560 if (SubReg != 0) { 0
561 LaneBitmask LaneMask = TRI->getSubRegIndexLaneMask(SubReg); 0
562 if ((LaneMask & SR.LaneMask).none()) 0
563 continue; 0
564 } ----
565 // We only need to visit each instruction once. ----
566 MachineInstr *UseMI = MO.getParent(); 0
567 SlotIndex Idx = getInstructionIndex(*UseMI).getRegSlot(); 0
568 if (Idx == LastIdx) 0
569 continue; 0
570 LastIdx = Idx; 0
571 ----
572 LiveQueryResult LRQ = SR.Query(Idx); 0
573 VNInfo *VNI = LRQ.valueIn(); 0
574 // For Subranges it is possible that only undef values are left in that ----
575 // part of the subregister, so there is no real liverange at the use ----
576 if (!VNI) 0
577 continue; 0
578 ----
579 // Special case: An early-clobber tied operand reads and writes the ----
580 // register one slot early. ----
581 if (VNInfo *DefVNI = LRQ.valueDefined()) 0
582 Idx = DefVNI->def; 0
583 ----
584 WorkList.push_back(std::make_pair(Idx, VNI)); 0
585 } ----
586 ----
587 // Create a new live ranges with only minimal live segments per def. ----
588 LiveRange NewLR; 0
589 createSegmentsForValues(NewLR, SR.vnis()); 0
590 extendSegmentsToUses(NewLR, WorkList, Reg, SR.LaneMask); 0
591 ----
592 // Move the trimmed ranges back. ----
593 SR.segments.swap(NewLR.segments); 0
594 ----
595 // Remove dead PHI value numbers ----
596 for (VNInfo *VNI : SR.valnos) { 0
597 if (VNI->isUnused()) 0
598 continue; 0
599 const LiveRange::Segment *Segment = SR.getSegmentContaining(VNI->def); 0
600 assert(Segment != nullptr && "Missing segment for VNI"); 0
601 if (Segment->end != VNI->def.getDeadSlot()) 0
602 continue; 0
603 if (VNI->isPHIDef()) { 0
604 // This is a dead PHI. Remove it. ----
605 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Dead PHI at " << VNI->def 0
606 << " may separate interval\n"); ----
607 VNI->markUnused(); 0
608 SR.removeSegment(*Segment); 0
609 } ----
610 } ----
611 ----
612 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Shrunk: " << SR << '\n'); 0
613 } 0

619 LICalc->reset(MF, getSlotIndexes(), DomTree, &getVNInfoAllocator()); 0
620 for (SlotIndex Idx : Indices) 0
621 LICalc->extend(LR, Idx, /*PhysReg=*/0, Undefs); 0
622 } 0
623 ----
624 void LiveIntervals::pruneValue(LiveRange &LR, SlotIndex Kill, 0
625 SmallVectorImpl *EndPoints) { ----
626 LiveQueryResult LRQ = LR.Query(Kill); 0
627 VNInfo *VNI = LRQ.valueOutOrDead(); 0
628 if (!VNI) 0
629 return; 0
630 ----
631 MachineBasicBlock *KillMBB = Indexes->getMBBFromIndex(Kill); 0
632 SlotIndex MBBEnd = Indexes->getMBBEndIdx(KillMBB); 0
633 ----
634 // If VNI isn't live out from KillMBB, the value is trivially pruned. ----
635 if (LRQ.endPoint() < MBBEnd) { 0
636 LR.removeSegment(Kill, LRQ.endPoint()); 0
637 if (EndPoints) EndPoints->push_back(LRQ.endPoint()); 0
638 return; 0
639 } ----
640 ----
641 // VNI is live out of KillMBB. ----
642 LR.removeSegment(Kill, MBBEnd); 0
643 if (EndPoints) EndPoints->push_back(MBBEnd); 0
644 ----
645 // Find all blocks that are reachable from KillMBB without leaving VNI's live ----
646 // range. It is possible that KillMBB itself is reachable, so start a DFS ----
647 // from each successor. ----
648 using VisitedTy = df_iterator_default_set; ----
649 VisitedTy Visited; 0
650 for (MachineBasicBlock *Succ : KillMBB->successors()) { 0
651 for (df_ext_iterator 0
652 I = df_ext_begin(Succ, Visited), E = df_ext_end(Succ, Visited); 0
653 I != E;) { 0
654 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = *I; 0
655 ----
656 // Check if VNI is live in to MBB. ----
657 SlotIndex MBBStart, MBBEnd; 0
658 std::tie(MBBStart, MBBEnd) = Indexes->getMBBRange(MBB); 0
659 LiveQueryResult LRQ = LR.Query(MBBStart); 0
660 if (LRQ.valueIn() != VNI) { 0
661 // This block isn't part of the VNI segment. Prune the search. ----
662 I.skipChildren(); 0
663 continue; 0
664 } ----
665 ----
666 // Prune the search if VNI is killed in MBB. ----
667 if (LRQ.endPoint() < MBBEnd) { 0
668 LR.removeSegment(MBBStart, LRQ.endPoint()); 0
669 if (EndPoints) EndPoints->push_back(LRQ.endPoint()); 0
670 I.skipChildren(); 0
671 continue; 0
672 } ----
673 ----
674 // VNI is live through MBB. ----
675 LR.removeSegment(MBBStart, MBBEnd); 0
676 if (EndPoints) EndPoints->push_back(MBBEnd); 0
677 ++I; 0
678 } 0
679 } ----
680 } 0

879 /// Check whether use of reg in MI is live-through. Live-through means that ----
880 /// the value is alive on exit from Machine instruction. The example of such ----
881 /// use is a deopt value in statepoint instruction. ----
882 static bool hasLiveThroughUse(const MachineInstr *MI, Register Reg) { 0
883 if (MI->getOpcode() != TargetOpcode::STATEPOINT) 0
884 return false; 0
885 StatepointOpers SO(MI); 0
886 if (SO.getFlags() & (uint64_t)StatepointFlags::DeoptLiveIn) 0
887 return false; 0
888 for (unsigned Idx = SO.getNumDeoptArgsIdx(), E = SO.getNumGCPtrIdx(); Idx < E; 0
889 ++Idx) { ----
890 const MachineOperand &MO = MI->getOperand(Idx); 0
891 if (MO.isReg() && MO.getReg() == Reg) 0
892 return true; 0
893 } ----
894 return false; 0
895 } ----
896 ----
897 bool LiveIntervals::checkRegMaskInterference(const LiveInterval &LI, 16 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
898 BitVector &UsableRegs) { ----
899 if (LI.empty()) 16 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
900 return false; 0
901 LiveInterval::const_iterator LiveI = LI.begin(), LiveE = LI.end(); 16 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
902 ----
903 // Use a smaller arrays for local live ranges. ----
904 ArrayRef Slots; 16 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
905 ArrayRef Bits; 16 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
906 if (MachineBasicBlock *MBB = intervalIsInOneMBB(LI)) { 16 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
907 Slots = getRegMaskSlotsInBlock(MBB->getNumber()); 16 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
908 Bits = getRegMaskBitsInBlock(MBB->getNumber()); 16 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
909 } else { ----
910 Slots = getRegMaskSlots(); 0
911 Bits = getRegMaskBits(); 0
912 } ----
913 ----
914 // We are going to enumerate all the register mask slots contained in LI. ----
915 // Start with a binary search of RegMaskSlots to find a starting point. ----
916 ArrayRef::iterator SlotI = llvm::lower_bound(Slots, LiveI->start); 16 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
917 ArrayRef::iterator SlotE = Slots.end(); 16 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
918 ----
919 // No slots in range, LI begins after the last call. ----
920 if (SlotI == SlotE) 16 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
921 return false; 16 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
922 ----
923 bool Found = false; 0
924 // Utility to union regmasks. ----
925 auto unionBitMask = [&](unsigned Idx) { 0
926 if (!Found) { 0
927 // This is the first overlap. Initialize UsableRegs to all ones. ----
928 UsableRegs.clear(); 0
929 UsableRegs.resize(TRI->getNumRegs(), true); 0
930 Found = true; 0
931 } ----
932 // Remove usable registers clobbered by this mask. ----
933 UsableRegs.clearBitsNotInMask(Bits[Idx]); 0
934 }; 0
935 while (true) { ----
936 assert(*SlotI >= LiveI->start); 0
937 // Loop over all slots overlapping this segment. ----
938 while (*SlotI < LiveI->end) { 0
939 // *SlotI overlaps LI. Collect mask bits. ----
940 unionBitMask(SlotI - Slots.begin()); 0
941 if (++SlotI == SlotE) 0
942 return Found; 0
943 } ----
944 // If segment ends with live-through use we need to collect its regmask. ----
945 if (*SlotI == LiveI->end) 0
946 if (MachineInstr *MI = getInstructionFromIndex(*SlotI)) 0
947 if (hasLiveThroughUse(MI, LI.reg())) 0
948 unionBitMask(SlotI++ - Slots.begin()); 0
949 // *SlotI is beyond the current LI segment. ----
950 // Special advance implementation to not miss next LiveI->end. ----
951 if (++LiveI == LiveE || SlotI == SlotE || *SlotI > LI.endIndex()) 0
952 return Found; 0
953 while (LiveI->end < *SlotI) 0
954 ++LiveI; 0
955 // Advance SlotI until it overlaps. ----
956 while (*SlotI < LiveI->start) 0
957 if (++SlotI == SlotE) 0
958 return Found; 0
959 } 0
960 } ----

966 /// Toolkit used by handleMove to trim or extend live intervals. ----
967 class LiveIntervals::HMEditor { ----
968 private: ----
969 LiveIntervals& LIS; ----
970 const MachineRegisterInfo& MRI; ----
971 const TargetRegisterInfo& TRI; ----
972 SlotIndex OldIdx; ----
973 SlotIndex NewIdx; ----
974 SmallPtrSet Updated; ----
975 bool UpdateFlags; ----
976 ----
977 public: ----
978 HMEditor(LiveIntervals& LIS, const MachineRegisterInfo& MRI, 0
979 const TargetRegisterInfo& TRI, ----
980 SlotIndex OldIdx, SlotIndex NewIdx, bool UpdateFlags) ----
981 : LIS(LIS), MRI(MRI), TRI(TRI), OldIdx(OldIdx), NewIdx(NewIdx), 0
982 UpdateFlags(UpdateFlags) {} 0
983 ----
984 // FIXME: UpdateFlags is a workaround that creates live intervals for all ----
985 // physregs, even those that aren't needed for regalloc, in order to update ----
986 // kill flags. This is wasteful. Eventually, LiveVariables will strip all kill ----
987 // flags, and postRA passes will use a live register utility instead. ----
988 LiveRange *getRegUnitLI(unsigned Unit) { 0
989 if (UpdateFlags && !MRI.isReservedRegUnit(Unit)) 0
990 return &LIS.getRegUnit(Unit); 0
991 return LIS.getCachedRegUnit(Unit); 0
992 } ----
993 ----
994 /// Update all live ranges touched by MI, assuming a move from OldIdx to ----
995 /// NewIdx. ----
996 void updateAllRanges(MachineInstr *MI) { 0
997 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "handleMove " << OldIdx << " -> " << NewIdx << ": " 0
998 << *MI); ----
999 bool hasRegMask = false; 0
1000 for (MachineOperand &MO : MI->operands()) { 0
1001 if (MO.isRegMask()) 0
1002 hasRegMask = true; 0
1003 if (!MO.isReg()) 0
1004 continue; 0
1005 if (MO.isUse()) { 0
1006 if (!MO.readsReg()) 0
1007 continue; 0
1008 // Aggressively clear all kill flags. ----
1009 // They are reinserted by VirtRegRewriter. ----
1010 MO.setIsKill(false); 0
1011 } ----
1012 ----
1013 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
1014 if (!Reg) 0
1015 continue; 0
1016 if (Reg.isVirtual()) { 0
1017 LiveInterval &LI = LIS.getInterval(Reg); 0
1018 if (LI.hasSubRanges()) { 0
1019 unsigned SubReg = MO.getSubReg(); 0
1020 LaneBitmask LaneMask = SubReg ? TRI.getSubRegIndexLaneMask(SubReg) 0
1021 : MRI.getMaxLaneMaskForVReg(Reg); 0
1022 for (LiveInterval::SubRange &S : LI.subranges()) { 0
1023 if ((S.LaneMask & LaneMask).none()) 0
1024 continue; 0
1025 updateRange(S, Reg, S.LaneMask); 0
1026 } ----
1027 } ----
1028 updateRange(LI, Reg, LaneBitmask::getNone()); 0
1029 // If main range has a hole and we are moving a subrange use across ----
1030 // the hole updateRange() cannot properly handle it since it only ----
1031 // gets the LiveRange and not the whole LiveInterval. As a result ----
1032 // we may end up with a main range not covering all subranges. ----
1033 // This is extremely rare case, so let's check and reconstruct the ----
1034 // main range. ----
1035 if (LI.hasSubRanges()) { 0
1036 unsigned SubReg = MO.getSubReg(); 0
1037 LaneBitmask LaneMask = SubReg ? TRI.getSubRegIndexLaneMask(SubReg) 0
1038 : MRI.getMaxLaneMaskForVReg(Reg); 0
1039 for (LiveInterval::SubRange &S : LI.subranges()) { 0
1040 if ((S.LaneMask & LaneMask).none() || LI.covers(S)) 0
1041 continue; 0
1042 LI.clear(); 0
1043 LIS.constructMainRangeFromSubranges(LI); 0
1044 break; 0
1045 } ----
1046 } ----
1047 ----
1048 continue; 0
1049 } 0
1050 ----
1051 // For physregs, only update the regunits that actually have a ----
1052 // precomputed live range. ----
1053 for (MCRegUnit Unit : TRI.regunits(Reg.asMCReg())) 0
1054 if (LiveRange *LR = getRegUnitLI(Unit)) 0
1055 updateRange(*LR, Unit, LaneBitmask::getNone()); 0
1056 } ----
1057 if (hasRegMask) 0
1058 updateRegMaskSlots(); 0
1059 } 0
1060 ----
1061 private: ----
1062 /// Update a single live range, assuming an instruction has been moved from ----
1063 /// OldIdx to NewIdx. ----
1064 void updateRange(LiveRange &LR, Register Reg, LaneBitmask LaneMask) { 0
1065 if (!Updated.insert(&LR).second) 0
1066 return; 0
1067 LLVM_DEBUG({ 0
1068 dbgs() << " "; ----
1069 if (Reg.isVirtual()) { ----
1070 dbgs() << printReg(Reg); ----
1071 if (LaneMask.any()) ----
1072 dbgs() << " L" << PrintLaneMask(LaneMask); ----
1073 } else { ----
1074 dbgs() << printRegUnit(Reg, &TRI); ----
1075 } ----
1076 dbgs() << ":\t" << LR << '\n'; ----
1077 }); ----
1078 if (SlotIndex::isEarlierInstr(OldIdx, NewIdx)) 0
1079 handleMoveDown(LR); 0
1080 else ----
1081 handleMoveUp(LR, Reg, LaneMask); 0
1082 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " -->\t" << LR << '\n'); 0
1083 LR.verify(); 0
1084 } ----
1085 ----
1086 /// Update LR to reflect an instruction has been moved downwards from OldIdx ----
1087 /// to NewIdx (OldIdx < NewIdx). ----
1088 void handleMoveDown(LiveRange &LR) { 0
1089 LiveRange::iterator E = LR.end(); 0
1090 // Segment going into OldIdx. ----
1091 LiveRange::iterator OldIdxIn = LR.find(OldIdx.getBaseIndex()); 0
1092 ----
1093 // No value live before or after OldIdx? Nothing to do. ----
1094 if (OldIdxIn == E || SlotIndex::isEarlierInstr(OldIdx, OldIdxIn->start)) 0
1095 return; 0
1096 ----
1097 LiveRange::iterator OldIdxOut; ----
1098 // Do we have a value live-in to OldIdx? ----
1099 if (SlotIndex::isEarlierInstr(OldIdxIn->start, OldIdx)) { 0
1100 // If the live-in value already extends to NewIdx, there is nothing to do. ----
1101 if (SlotIndex::isEarlierEqualInstr(NewIdx, OldIdxIn->end)) 0
1102 return; 0
1103 // Aggressively remove all kill flags from the old kill point. ----
1104 // Kill flags shouldn't be used while live intervals exist, they will be ----
1105 // reinserted by VirtRegRewriter. ----
1106 if (MachineInstr *KillMI = LIS.getInstructionFromIndex(OldIdxIn->end)) 0
1107 for (MachineOperand &MOP : mi_bundle_ops(*KillMI)) 0
1108 if (MOP.isReg() && MOP.isUse()) 0
1109 MOP.setIsKill(false); 0
1110 ----
1111 // Is there a def before NewIdx which is not OldIdx? ----
1112 LiveRange::iterator Next = std::next(OldIdxIn); 0
1113 if (Next != E && !SlotIndex::isSameInstr(OldIdx, Next->start) && 0
1114 SlotIndex::isEarlierInstr(Next->start, NewIdx)) { 0
1115 // If we are here then OldIdx was just a use but not a def. We only have ----
1116 // to ensure liveness extends to NewIdx. ----
1117 LiveRange::iterator NewIdxIn = ----
1118 LR.advanceTo(Next, NewIdx.getBaseIndex()); 0
1119 // Extend the segment before NewIdx if necessary. ----
1120 if (NewIdxIn == E || 0
1121 !SlotIndex::isEarlierInstr(NewIdxIn->start, NewIdx)) { 0
1122 LiveRange::iterator Prev = std::prev(NewIdxIn); 0
1123 Prev->end = NewIdx.getRegSlot(); 0
1124 } ----
1125 // Extend OldIdxIn. ----
1126 OldIdxIn->end = Next->start; 0
1127 return; 0
1128 } ----
1129 ----
1130 // Adjust OldIdxIn->end to reach NewIdx. This may temporarily make LR ----
1131 // invalid by overlapping ranges. ----
1132 bool isKill = SlotIndex::isSameInstr(OldIdx, OldIdxIn->end); 0
1133 OldIdxIn->end = NewIdx.getRegSlot(OldIdxIn->end.isEarlyClobber()); 0
1134 // If this was not a kill, then there was no def and we're done. ----
1135 if (!isKill) 0
1136 return; 0
1137 ----
1138 // Did we have a Def at OldIdx? ----
1139 OldIdxOut = Next; 0
1140 if (OldIdxOut == E || !SlotIndex::isSameInstr(OldIdx, OldIdxOut->start)) 0
1141 return; 0
1142 } else { ----
1143 OldIdxOut = OldIdxIn; 0
1144 } ----
1145 ----
1146 // If we are here then there is a Definition at OldIdx. OldIdxOut points ----
1147 // to the segment starting there. ----
1148 assert(OldIdxOut != E && SlotIndex::isSameInstr(OldIdx, OldIdxOut->start) && 0
1149 "No def?"); ----
1150 VNInfo *OldIdxVNI = OldIdxOut->valno; 0
1151 assert(OldIdxVNI->def == OldIdxOut->start && "Inconsistent def"); 0
1152 ----
1153 // If the defined value extends beyond NewIdx, just move the beginning ----
1154 // of the segment to NewIdx. ----
1155 SlotIndex NewIdxDef = NewIdx.getRegSlot(OldIdxOut->start.isEarlyClobber()); 0
1156 if (SlotIndex::isEarlierInstr(NewIdxDef, OldIdxOut->end)) { 0
1157 OldIdxVNI->def = NewIdxDef; 0
1158 OldIdxOut->start = OldIdxVNI->def; 0
1159 return; 0
1160 } ----
1161 ----
1162 // If we are here then we have a Definition at OldIdx which ends before ----
1163 // NewIdx. ----
1164 ----
1165 // Is there an existing Def at NewIdx? ----
1166 LiveRange::iterator AfterNewIdx ----
1167 = LR.advanceTo(OldIdxOut, NewIdx.getRegSlot()); 0
1168 bool OldIdxDefIsDead = OldIdxOut->end.isDead(); 0
1169 if (!OldIdxDefIsDead && 0
1170 SlotIndex::isEarlierInstr(OldIdxOut->end, NewIdxDef)) { 0
1171 // OldIdx is not a dead def, and NewIdxDef is inside a new interval. ----
1172 VNInfo *DefVNI; ----
1173 if (OldIdxOut != LR.begin() && 0
1174 !SlotIndex::isEarlierInstr(std::prev(OldIdxOut)->end, 0
1175 OldIdxOut->start)) { ----
1176 // There is no gap between OldIdxOut and its predecessor anymore, ----
1177 // merge them. ----
1178 LiveRange::iterator IPrev = std::prev(OldIdxOut); 0
1179 DefVNI = OldIdxVNI; 0
1180 IPrev->end = OldIdxOut->end; 0
1181 } else { ----
1182 // The value is live in to OldIdx ----
1183 LiveRange::iterator INext = std::next(OldIdxOut); 0
1184 assert(INext != E && "Must have following segment"); 0
1185 // We merge OldIdxOut and its successor. As we're dealing with subreg ----
1186 // reordering, there is always a successor to OldIdxOut in the same BB ----
1187 // We don't need INext->valno anymore and will reuse for the new segment ----
1188 // we create later. ----
1189 DefVNI = OldIdxVNI; 0
1190 INext->start = OldIdxOut->end; 0
1191 INext->valno->def = INext->start; 0
1192 } ----
1193 // If NewIdx is behind the last segment, extend that and append a new one. ----
1194 if (AfterNewIdx == E) { 0
1195 // OldIdxOut is undef at this point, Slide (OldIdxOut;AfterNewIdx] up ----
1196 // one position. ----
1197 // |- ?/OldIdxOut -| |- X0 -| ... |- Xn -| end ----
1198 // => |- X0/OldIdxOut -| ... |- Xn -| |- undef/NewS -| end ----
1199 std::copy(std::next(OldIdxOut), E, OldIdxOut); 0
1200 // The last segment is undefined now, reuse it for a dead def. ----
1201 LiveRange::iterator NewSegment = std::prev(E); 0
1202 *NewSegment = LiveRange::Segment(NewIdxDef, NewIdxDef.getDeadSlot(), 0
1203 DefVNI); ----
1204 DefVNI->def = NewIdxDef; 0
1205 ----
1206 LiveRange::iterator Prev = std::prev(NewSegment); 0
1207 Prev->end = NewIdxDef; 0
1208 } else { ----
1209 // OldIdxOut is undef at this point, Slide (OldIdxOut;AfterNewIdx] up ----
1210 // one position. ----
1211 // |- ?/OldIdxOut -| |- X0 -| ... |- Xn/AfterNewIdx -| |- Next -| ----
1212 // => |- X0/OldIdxOut -| ... |- Xn -| |- Xn/AfterNewIdx -| |- Next -| ----
1213 std::copy(std::next(OldIdxOut), std::next(AfterNewIdx), OldIdxOut); 0
1214 LiveRange::iterator Prev = std::prev(AfterNewIdx); 0
1215 // We have two cases: ----
1216 if (SlotIndex::isEarlierInstr(Prev->start, NewIdxDef)) { 0
1217 // Case 1: NewIdx is inside a liverange. Split this liverange at ----
1218 // NewIdxDef into the segment "Prev" followed by "NewSegment". ----
1219 LiveRange::iterator NewSegment = AfterNewIdx; 0
1220 *NewSegment = LiveRange::Segment(NewIdxDef, Prev->end, Prev->valno); 0
1221 Prev->valno->def = NewIdxDef; 0
1222 ----
1223 *Prev = LiveRange::Segment(Prev->start, NewIdxDef, DefVNI); 0
1224 DefVNI->def = Prev->start; 0
1225 } else { ----
1226 // Case 2: NewIdx is in a lifetime hole. Keep AfterNewIdx as is and ----
1227 // turn Prev into a segment from NewIdx to AfterNewIdx->start. ----
1228 *Prev = LiveRange::Segment(NewIdxDef, AfterNewIdx->start, DefVNI); 0
1229 DefVNI->def = NewIdxDef; 0
1230 assert(DefVNI != AfterNewIdx->valno); 0
1231 } ----
1232 } ----
1233 return; 0
1234 } ----
1235 ----
1236 if (AfterNewIdx != E && 0
1237 SlotIndex::isSameInstr(AfterNewIdx->start, NewIdxDef)) { 0
1238 // There is an existing def at NewIdx. The def at OldIdx is coalesced into ----
1239 // that value. ----
1240 assert(AfterNewIdx->valno != OldIdxVNI && "Multiple defs of value?"); 0
1241 LR.removeValNo(OldIdxVNI); 0
1242 } else { ----
1243 // There was no existing def at NewIdx. We need to create a dead def ----
1244 // at NewIdx. Shift segments over the old OldIdxOut segment, this frees ----
1245 // a new segment at the place where we want to construct the dead def. ----
1246 // |- OldIdxOut -| |- X0 -| ... |- Xn -| |- AfterNewIdx -| ----
1247 // => |- X0/OldIdxOut -| ... |- Xn -| |- undef/NewS. -| |- AfterNewIdx -| ----
1248 assert(AfterNewIdx != OldIdxOut && "Inconsistent iterators"); 0
1249 std::copy(std::next(OldIdxOut), AfterNewIdx, OldIdxOut); 0
1250 // We can reuse OldIdxVNI now. ----
1251 LiveRange::iterator NewSegment = std::prev(AfterNewIdx); 0
1252 VNInfo *NewSegmentVNI = OldIdxVNI; 0
1253 NewSegmentVNI->def = NewIdxDef; 0
1254 *NewSegment = LiveRange::Segment(NewIdxDef, NewIdxDef.getDeadSlot(), 0
1255 NewSegmentVNI); ----
1256 } ----
1257 } ----
1258 ----
1259 /// Update LR to reflect an instruction has been moved upwards from OldIdx ----
1260 /// to NewIdx (NewIdx < OldIdx). ----
1261 void handleMoveUp(LiveRange &LR, Register Reg, LaneBitmask LaneMask) { 0
1262 LiveRange::iterator E = LR.end(); 0
1263 // Segment going into OldIdx. ----
1264 LiveRange::iterator OldIdxIn = LR.find(OldIdx.getBaseIndex()); 0
1265 ----
1266 // No value live before or after OldIdx? Nothing to do. ----
1267 if (OldIdxIn == E || SlotIndex::isEarlierInstr(OldIdx, OldIdxIn->start)) 0
1268 return; 0
1269 ----
1270 LiveRange::iterator OldIdxOut; ----
1271 // Do we have a value live-in to OldIdx? ----
1272 if (SlotIndex::isEarlierInstr(OldIdxIn->start, OldIdx)) { 0
1273 // If the live-in value isn't killed here, then we have no Def at ----
1274 // OldIdx, moreover the value must be live at NewIdx so there is nothing ----
1275 // to do. ----
1276 bool isKill = SlotIndex::isSameInstr(OldIdx, OldIdxIn->end); 0
1277 if (!isKill) 0
1278 return; 0
1279 ----
1280 // At this point we have to move OldIdxIn->end back to the nearest ----
1281 // previous use or (dead-)def but no further than NewIdx. ----
1282 SlotIndex DefBeforeOldIdx ----
1283 = std::max(OldIdxIn->start.getDeadSlot(), 0
1284 NewIdx.getRegSlot(OldIdxIn->end.isEarlyClobber())); 0
1285 OldIdxIn->end = findLastUseBefore(DefBeforeOldIdx, Reg, LaneMask); 0
1286 ----
1287 // Did we have a Def at OldIdx? If not we are done now. ----
1288 OldIdxOut = std::next(OldIdxIn); 0
1289 if (OldIdxOut == E || !SlotIndex::isSameInstr(OldIdx, OldIdxOut->start)) 0
1290 return; 0
1291 } else { ----
1292 OldIdxOut = OldIdxIn; 0
1293 OldIdxIn = OldIdxOut != LR.begin() ? std::prev(OldIdxOut) : E; 0
1294 } ----
1295 ----
1296 // If we are here then there is a Definition at OldIdx. OldIdxOut points ----
1297 // to the segment starting there. ----
1298 assert(OldIdxOut != E && SlotIndex::isSameInstr(OldIdx, OldIdxOut->start) && 0
1299 "No def?"); ----
1300 VNInfo *OldIdxVNI = OldIdxOut->valno; 0
1301 assert(OldIdxVNI->def == OldIdxOut->start && "Inconsistent def"); 0
1302 bool OldIdxDefIsDead = OldIdxOut->end.isDead(); 0
1303 ----
1304 // Is there an existing def at NewIdx? ----
1305 SlotIndex NewIdxDef = NewIdx.getRegSlot(OldIdxOut->start.isEarlyClobber()); 0
1306 LiveRange::iterator NewIdxOut = LR.find(NewIdx.getRegSlot()); 0
1307 if (SlotIndex::isSameInstr(NewIdxOut->start, NewIdx)) { 0
1308 assert(NewIdxOut->valno != OldIdxVNI && 0
1309 "Same value defined more than once?"); ----
1310 // If OldIdx was a dead def remove it. ----
1311 if (!OldIdxDefIsDead) { 0
1312 // Remove segment starting at NewIdx and move begin of OldIdxOut to ----
1313 // NewIdx so it can take its place. ----
1314 OldIdxVNI->def = NewIdxDef; 0
1315 OldIdxOut->start = NewIdxDef; 0
1316 LR.removeValNo(NewIdxOut->valno); 0
1317 } else { ----
1318 // Simply remove the dead def at OldIdx. ----
1319 LR.removeValNo(OldIdxVNI); 0
1320 } ----
1321 } else { ----
1322 // Previously nothing was live after NewIdx, so all we have to do now is ----
1323 // move the begin of OldIdxOut to NewIdx. ----
1324 if (!OldIdxDefIsDead) { 0
1325 // Do we have any intermediate Defs between OldIdx and NewIdx? ----
1326 if (OldIdxIn != E && 0
1327 SlotIndex::isEarlierInstr(NewIdxDef, OldIdxIn->start)) { 0
1328 // OldIdx is not a dead def and NewIdx is before predecessor start. ----
1329 LiveRange::iterator NewIdxIn = NewIdxOut; 0
1330 assert(NewIdxIn == LR.find(NewIdx.getBaseIndex())); 0
1331 const SlotIndex SplitPos = NewIdxDef; 0
1332 OldIdxVNI = OldIdxIn->valno; 0
1333 ----
1334 SlotIndex NewDefEndPoint = std::next(NewIdxIn)->end; 0
1335 LiveRange::iterator Prev = std::prev(OldIdxIn); 0
1336 if (OldIdxIn != LR.begin() && 0
1337 SlotIndex::isEarlierInstr(NewIdx, Prev->end)) { 0
1338 // If the segment before OldIdx read a value defined earlier than ----
1339 // NewIdx, the moved instruction also reads and forwards that ----
1340 // value. Extend the lifetime of the new def point. ----
1341 ----
1342 // Extend to where the previous range started, unless there is ----
1343 // another redef first. ----
1344 NewDefEndPoint = std::min(OldIdxIn->start, 0
1345 std::next(NewIdxOut)->start); 0
1346 } ----
1347 ----
1348 // Merge the OldIdxIn and OldIdxOut segments into OldIdxOut. ----
1349 OldIdxOut->valno->def = OldIdxIn->start; 0
1350 *OldIdxOut = LiveRange::Segment(OldIdxIn->start, OldIdxOut->end, 0
1351 OldIdxOut->valno); ----
1352 // OldIdxIn and OldIdxVNI are now undef and can be overridden. ----
1353 // We Slide [NewIdxIn, OldIdxIn) down one position. ----
1354 // |- X0/NewIdxIn -| ... |- Xn-1 -||- Xn/OldIdxIn -||- OldIdxOut -| ----
1355 // => |- undef/NexIdxIn -| |- X0 -| ... |- Xn-1 -| |- Xn/OldIdxOut -| ----
1356 std::copy_backward(NewIdxIn, OldIdxIn, OldIdxOut); 0
1357 // NewIdxIn is now considered undef so we can reuse it for the moved ----
1358 // value. ----
1359 LiveRange::iterator NewSegment = NewIdxIn; 0
1360 LiveRange::iterator Next = std::next(NewSegment); 0
1361 if (SlotIndex::isEarlierInstr(Next->start, NewIdx)) { 0
1362 // There is no gap between NewSegment and its predecessor. ----
1363 *NewSegment = LiveRange::Segment(Next->start, SplitPos, 0
1364 Next->valno); ----
1365 ----
1366 *Next = LiveRange::Segment(SplitPos, NewDefEndPoint, OldIdxVNI); 0
1367 Next->valno->def = SplitPos; 0
1368 } else { ----
1369 // There is a gap between NewSegment and its predecessor ----
1370 // Value becomes live in. ----
1371 *NewSegment = LiveRange::Segment(SplitPos, Next->start, OldIdxVNI); 0
1372 NewSegment->valno->def = SplitPos; 0
1373 } ----
1374 } else { ----
1375 // Leave the end point of a live def. ----
1376 OldIdxOut->start = NewIdxDef; 0
1377 OldIdxVNI->def = NewIdxDef; 0
1378 if (OldIdxIn != E && SlotIndex::isEarlierInstr(NewIdx, OldIdxIn->end)) 0
1379 OldIdxIn->end = NewIdxDef; 0
1380 } ----
1381 } else if (OldIdxIn != E 0
1382 && SlotIndex::isEarlierInstr(NewIdxOut->start, NewIdx) 0
1383 && SlotIndex::isEarlierInstr(NewIdx, NewIdxOut->end)) { 0
1384 // OldIdxVNI is a dead def that has been moved into the middle of ----
1385 // another value in LR. That can happen when LR is a whole register, ----
1386 // but the dead def is a write to a subreg that is dead at NewIdx. ----
1387 // The dead def may have been moved across other values ----
1388 // in LR, so move OldIdxOut up to NewIdxOut. Slide [NewIdxOut;OldIdxOut) ----
1389 // down one position. ----
1390 // |- X0/NewIdxOut -| ... |- Xn-1 -| |- Xn/OldIdxOut -| |- next - | ----
1391 // => |- X0/NewIdxOut -| |- X0 -| ... |- Xn-1 -| |- next -| ----
1392 std::copy_backward(NewIdxOut, OldIdxOut, std::next(OldIdxOut)); 0
1393 // Modify the segment at NewIdxOut and the following segment to meet at ----
1394 // the point of the dead def, with the following segment getting ----
1395 // OldIdxVNI as its value number. ----
1396 *NewIdxOut = LiveRange::Segment( 0

1402 for (auto *Idx = NewIdxOut + 2; Idx <= OldIdxOut; ++Idx) 0
1403 Idx->valno = OldIdxVNI; 0
1404 // Aggressively remove all dead flags from the former dead definition. ----
1405 // Kill/dead flags shouldn't be used while live intervals exist; they ----
1406 // will be reinserted by VirtRegRewriter. ----
1407 if (MachineInstr *KillMI = LIS.getInstructionFromIndex(NewIdx)) 0
1408 for (MIBundleOperands MO(*KillMI); MO.isValid(); ++MO) 0
1409 if (MO->isReg() && !MO->isUse()) 0

1411 } else { ----
1412 // OldIdxVNI is a dead def. It may have been moved across other values ----
1413 // in LR, so move OldIdxOut up to NewIdxOut. Slide [NewIdxOut;OldIdxOut) ----
1414 // down one position. ----
1415 // |- X0/NewIdxOut -| ... |- Xn-1 -| |- Xn/OldIdxOut -| |- next - | ----
1416 // => |- undef/NewIdxOut -| |- X0 -| ... |- Xn-1 -| |- next -| ----
1417 std::copy_backward(NewIdxOut, OldIdxOut, std::next(OldIdxOut)); 0

1419 LiveRange::iterator NewSegment = NewIdxOut; 0

1422 NewSegmentVNI); ----
1423 NewSegmentVNI->def = NewIdxDef; 0
1424 } ----
1425 } ----

1428 void updateRegMaskSlots() { 0
1429 SmallVectorImpl::iterator RI = ----

1442 // Return the last use of reg between NewIdx and OldIdx. ----
1443 SlotIndex findLastUseBefore(SlotIndex Before, Register Reg, 0
1444 LaneBitmask LaneMask) { ----
1445 if (Reg.isVirtual()) { 0

1447 for (MachineOperand &MO : MRI.use_nodbg_operands(Reg)) { 0
1448 if (MO.isUndef()) 0

1454 ----

1461 } ----
1462 ----
1463 // This is a regunit interval, so scanning the use list could be very ----
1464 // expensive. Scan upwards from OldIdx instead. ----
1465 assert(Before < OldIdx && "Expected upwards move"); 0
1466 SlotIndexes *Indexes = LIS.getSlotIndexes(); 0

1468 ----
1469 // OldIdx may not correspond to an instruction any longer, so set MII to ----
1470 // point to the next instruction after OldIdx, or MBB->end(). ----

1482 ----
1483 // Stop searching when Before is reached. ----
1484 if (!SlotIndex::isEarlierInstr(Before, Idx)) 0
1485 return Before; 0
1486 ----
1487 // Check if MII uses Reg. ----
1488 for (MIBundleOperands MO(*MII); MO.isValid(); ++MO) 0
1489 if (MO->isReg() && !MO->isUndef() && MO->getReg().isPhysical() && 0
1490 TRI.hasRegUnit(MO->getReg(), Reg)) 0
1491 return Idx.getRegSlot(); 0
1492 } ----
1493 // Didn't reach Before. It must be the first instruction in the block. ----
1494 return Before; 0

1641 MachineBasicBlock::iterator Begin, ----
1642 MachineBasicBlock::iterator End, ----
1643 ArrayRef OrigRegs) { ----
